On the other hand I feel the same way about Insurrection... one of the least favorite Star Trek films among fans. Frankly I loved that it wasn't about the fate of the galaxy hanging in the balance for a change, and just the crew of the Enterprise at stake.

text: Ok.  I'm not a Star Trek fan.  I mean..I have nothing against it, but I just never really got into it.  Weird, considering I'm a huge Sci-Fi nut.  I've read in the past that major Trek fans had some serious issues with the Abrams Trek movies.  Can someone explain in a nutshell why?  I thought they were pretty fantastic and even though I know very little about Star Trek, I felt like Abrams tried hard to honor source material and really give the characters the personalities and vibe of their respective past counterparts….purely biased on the very little I've seen.  LOL.  I grew up watching a Trek movie in the theatre here and there…watched maybe 20-30 episodes of Next Generation throughout my years, due to my father being a big fan of that series…but I'd like to know why the hardcore Trek fans have so much hate for the Abrams movies.

text: Star Trek has always been one of my favourites, but i honestly don't want to watch that. Since the first episode it captured my imagination, introducing new concepts and ideas into my world without using all those special effects to get me interested. There have been episodes, like Tapestry, which really altered my world view, so i can't help feeling a bit betrayed when i see that it has been turned into yet another action movie, exciting to watch (especially in 4DX) but lacking in intellectual traits that have characterized Star Trek since the very beginning. Don't get me wrong i love the special effects, but are they really the only thing our times have to offer?

text: There were many things about this Star Trek that were an improvment from recent attempts.  I especially liked the view of the Enterprise at warp showing the nacels creating waves in reality.    Hovever, as a follower of the Trek since the beginning, there is something about this movie that kicked me right out of the story.  Somewhere around 50 minutes into Beyond, the saucer section lifts by a bunch of things that look like old rocket booster flames.  THE ENTERPRISE MOVES SUB-LIGHT VIA REACTIONLESS THRUSTERS, it always has.  Reactionless thrusters like the tie fighters in Star Wars, not reaction thrusters like on a present day rocket.  The effect is like watching that old classic The Sea Witch, and see as the ship goes by, that it's powered by a couple of outboard motors.  Dissapointing.

text: This movie was so bad it MADE ABSOLUTELY NOOOOO SENSE. AN THEY LEFT OUT SO MANY STORY PLOTS. Just a few that come to mind...IF THOSE LITTLE SHIPS TOOK OFF FROM THE PLANET THEN WHY WERE THEY BLOWING UP FOLLOWING THE ENTERPRISE AS IT WAS CRASHING ON THE PLANET? DIDNT THEY JUST TAKE OFF FROM THE PLANET? THEY SHOW A ZILLION OF THE ENEMIES SHIPS IN SPACE. EACH ONE WITH 1 TO 2 PILOTS IN THEM, THEN WHERE WAS THEIR HUGE CITY TO HOLD ALL THEIR SHIPS? THEY ONLY SHOWED A LITTLE DINKY TOWN. I MEAN COME ON THE ENEMY HAD BILLIONS OF SHIPS...WERE DID THEY ALL COME FROM? WHERE DID THE PEOPLE COME FROM? IF IT WAS FROM A PREVIOUS STAR SHIP...WHERE DID THE EXTRA BILLION ZILLION OTHER PEOPLE COME FROM TO FLY THOSE BILLION ZILLION OTHER SHIPS? HOW DID THOSE LITTLE TINY ENEMY SHIPS GET TO THE STAR BASE BALL BEFORE THE OLD STAR SHIP WHICH HAD WARP ENGINES? EACH OF THOSE TINY ENEMY SHIPS DIDNT HAVE WARP ENGINES...SO WOULDNT CAPTAIN KIRK IN THE OLD SHIP GET TO THE STAR BALL FIRST? SO WHAT ABOUT THE MAIN BAD GUY...OKAY HE WAS A HUMAN...DURING THE MOVIE HER TURNED BACK HUMAN? HOW? LOOK AT HIS TEETH IN THE BEGINNING BUT THE END OF THE MOVIE HE HAD PEARLY WHITE TEETH....WHAT HAPPEN TO HIS FANGS? HOW DID HE TRANSFORM BACK INTO A HUMAN? HIS BODY MORPHING MADE NO SENSE? SINCE THEY WERE OLD HUMANS AN THEY COULD SEND TRANSMISSIONS...WHY DIDNT THEY JUST GET HELP AN TELL THEM TO COME GET THEM. ESPECIALLY SINCE THEY ALREADY PICKED THAT 1 GIRL UP. SHE COULD HAVE BEEN LIKE HEY...THEY ARE YOUR OLD PEOPLE FROM 100 YEARS AGO....THEY HAVE GROWN INTO A BAZILLION PEOPLE FLYING A BAZILLION SHIPS...BUT INSTEAD OF COMING HOME AN FINDING THEIR FAMILY AN FRIENDS WHY WOULD THEY WANT TO DESTROY THEM. #1 IF THEY HAD THOSE BAZILLION LITTLE SHIPS THAT COULD FLY WARP DRIVE....THEN WHY IN GOD'S NAME DIDNT THEY GO HOME ALONG TIME AGO? THEY STAYED STRANDED JUST TO GET A WEAPON? THIS MOVIE JUST HAD WAY WAY WAY TOO MANY STUPID STORY HOLES WHICH MADE NO SENSE AT ALL. GREAT ACTIONS SCENES...BUT THE STORY WAS JUST SO STUPID AN MADE ABSOLUTELY NO SENSE. ESPECIALLY FOR BEING HUMANS WHO HAD SHIPS WHERE THEY COULD HAVE CAME HOME ALONG TIME AGO.
